EXPRESSION EVALUATOR
====================
// Author: Yuvaraja Subramaniam (www.linkedin.com/in/yuvaraja)

// Step 1: Build an expression tree for an expression
// Step 2: Evaluate the expression


1) Compiling / building the binary

	$ ./build.sh

2) Usage 
	$ ./expreval -h
       t - run tests
       d - print debug
       h - help

3) Running the test cases as well as user entered expression
	$ ./expreval -t

4) Runnng user entered expression alone
	$ ./expreval 


SAMPLE USAGE
============

./expreval 
======================== EVALUATE USER ENTERED EXPRESSION  ========================

Enter mathematical expression to evaluate : (8 * 2) - (2 * 3) + ( 9 / 3 )
Entered expression                        : (8 * 2) - (2 * 3) + ( 9 / 3 )
Successful AST tree construction for expression    : (8 * 2) - (2 * 3) + ( 9 / 3 )
AST TREE : 
--> --> --> --> 8
--> --> --> *
--> --> --> --> 2
--> --> -
--> --> --> --> 2
--> --> --> *
--> --> --> --> 3
--> +
--> --> --> 9
--> --> /
--> --> --> 3
Evaluated expression value               : 13

